name: Attorney General Daniel Cameron
tweet: Our Office of Consumer Protection is advising Kentuckians affected by the tornadoes and storms to closely monitor their credit for potential identity theft.  Access a free credit report by visiting  https://t.co/yATf9Ka7FP  Check out more tips here:  https://t.co/VQNFAoPwXK  https://t.co/kYbIKduYPF

name: Attorney General Daniel Cameron
tweet: Contractors can visit the licensing office in Mayfield Monday through Friday from 8:00 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. CT. The office will be closed on December 30 and 31. Read more:   https://t.co/8y3JEEhMEZ

name: Attorney General Daniel Cameron
tweet: ICYMI: We teamed up with Graves County and the City of Mayfield to launch a contractor registration program. We hope it will assist Kentuckians with identifying registered contractors and deter unscrupulous contractors from entering the region.

name: Attorney General Daniel Cameron
tweet: We’ve put together a brochure with information on the most common types of fraud and scams that occur after natural disasters.  Report suspected fraud to our Natural Disaster Fraud Hotline at 502-696-5485.  Check out the brochure here:  https://t.co/81OSM0pNe4

name: Attorney General Daniel Cameron
tweet: Beginning tomorrow at 12:00pm CT, contractors can visit the licensing office located at 1102 Paris Road, Suite 5 in Mayfield.  Read more:  https://t.co/EZuZTo7aBs (2/2)

name: Attorney General Daniel Cameron
tweet: We’re working with Graves County & the City of Mayfield to prevent home repair fraud by registering contractors that are working in tornado-damaged areas. (1/2)

name: Attorney General Daniel Cameron
tweet: There are several ways to report suspected Natural Disaster fraud and scams to our office.    Call 502-696-5485 or report online at  https://t.co/oUqXHk3g6C and  https://t.co/r74s39rn2X.  https://t.co/ShOWNNBBtA

name: Attorney General Daniel Cameron
tweet: From our family to yours, #MerryChristmas.  https://t.co/7tOYcTLMIr

name: Attorney General Daniel Cameron
tweet: This holiday season, consider helping those in need by donating blood.  Visit  https://t.co/0ODmyI2kED to learn more and to schedule your donation.  https://t.co/0mTqejDHli

name: Attorney General Daniel Cameron
tweet: If you’re doing last-minute holiday shopping today, keep an eye out for gift card scams. We joined @KYRETAIL and @KyChamber this week to launch a new initiative aimed at stopping these scams.    Learn more here:  https://t.co/rU2taECsTF

name: Attorney General Daniel Cameron
tweet: ICYMI: Kentucky’s Head Start programs serve over 17,000 Kentucky children, and we cannot afford to lose these essential services because of the Biden Administration’s vaccine mandate. This week, we filed a lawsuit challenging the mandate.  Read more:  https://t.co/008LRRMgnu

name: Attorney General Daniel Cameron
tweet: Breaking News: The U.S. Supreme Court will hear oral arguments on January 7th in our cases challenging the vaccine mandate for private employers and the mandate for healthcare workers.

name: Attorney General Daniel Cameron
tweet: Kentucky prosecutors should be given every reasonable tool to prosecute individuals who drive under the influence of drugs or alcohol. Today, we asked #SCOTUS to hear a case that strikes down important parts of KY's impaired driving laws.   Read more:  https://t.co/UqX15CB411  https://t.co/w8JETEauKe

name: Attorney General Daniel Cameron
tweet: Today, we filed a lawsuit challenging the Biden Administration's vaccine mandate for thousands of staff and volunteers in Head Start programs.  Read more:   https://t.co/hNC7Qbqbj6  https://t.co/IwQAmmnyqH

name: Attorney General Daniel Cameron
tweet: Today, the Search Warrant Task Force released its final report. The report provides eight recommendations related to the securing, reviewing, and serving of search warrants in the Commonwealth.  View the report here:   https://t.co/1MvCg1neCZ  https://t.co/7lHgIV3tOU

name: Attorney General Daniel Cameron
tweet: We’re partnering with @KYRETAIL and @KyChamber to  stop gift card scams.   Gift cards are the most frequently reported payment method for scams, and this new program will provide KY businesses and retailers with signage to post near gift card displays.  Check it out here:  https://t.co/yMVd84ayuF

name: Attorney General Daniel Cameron
tweet: Makenze and I join @LMPD in mourning the loss of Officer Zach Cottongim. We are praying for his entire family during this incredibly difficult time.    https://t.co/7UoJRSKwiN

name: Attorney General Daniel Cameron
tweet: Our Director of the Office of Senior Protection, LaDonna Koebel, spoke with @WHAS11 about our commitment to investigate and stop price gouging & scams.  Report suspected fraud to 502-696-5485 or  https://t.co/oUqXHk3g6C.    https://t.co/mwn155u00N

name: Attorney General Daniel Cameron
tweet: Early this morning, we asked the U.S. Supreme Court to immediately stop the vaccine mandate on private employers, after the Sixth Circuit ruled hours earlier that the mandate could go into effect.   See our filing here:   https://t.co/5iiQWOowRX  https://t.co/Nz2N4KaN32

name: Attorney General Daniel Cameron
tweet: Looting and theft will not be tolerated.   Our office has spoken with Graves County Sheriff Jon Hayden and Commonwealth’s Attorney Richie Kemp, and the full force of the law will be brought against anyone who tries to take advantage of Kentuckians.  https://t.co/v8NTzJ0Tge
